description:
Responsibilities

Handle full set of accounts;
Handle all daily accounting transactions, book keeping, data input and filing;
Prepare accounting vouchers and general ledger entries;
Prepare stock take and inventory report;
Year-end accounting report and audit schedule;
Assist in handling company administration works; 
Assist in other ad-hoc job projects as assigned.

Requirements

Diploma or above in accounting or relevant studies
At least 3-years of accounting experience
Acknowledged in MS Office Applications 
Good team player, self-initiative and strong communication
Prefer immediately available or in short-notice period candidate


Office Location: Causeway Bay

We offer an attractive remuneration package and excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send a detailed CV stating present & expected salary and date availability to us by email. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

職位: 首席執行官助理 / 實習生(CEO Assistant / Management Trainee)

我們集團目前正在尋找主席助理加入我們的集團。

圓核秀都集團總部設立於香港，自2012年以來不斷探索和拓展在中國大陸的娛樂演藝秀業務，通過收購、原創和改編等方式積累了大量娛樂演藝秀強IP群，涵蓋了大中小型娛樂演藝秀和室內外沉浸式燈光秀等不同類型的產品，並形成了具有自身特色的娛樂演藝消費場景品牌——《秀都》。 《秀都》品牌專案融合演藝高科技手段，滿足大眾消費轉型升級和振興夜間經濟的需求，高效佈局於中國大流量旅遊目的地城市。

我們為合適的候選人提供有吸引力的薪酬和附加福利。 如有興趣，請將完整的中文簡歷，現有和預期的薪資待遇和可上班日期發送電郵，或致電25988292陳小姐洽。

職責：  

處理主席所有文書工作，包括中英文信函及電郵回復及跟進
安排會議、草擬集團通告、撰寫商業項目報告、撰寫活動演詞等; 
準備會議議程，協調會議參與者（內部和外部），並根據需要管理會議提醒及會議記錄; 
協助準備演示材料;  每周主動跟進及檢視於商業專案各部門的進度，井及時向主席提出彙報及建議;
計劃、安排及協調國內及國外商務行程;
主席活動籌辦，包括但不限於預訂場地、協助佈置、聯絡嘉賓等
處理主席日常個人事務; 
隨同出席應酬活動;
負責對內及對外公關協調工作，維護與客戶的聯繫;
處理其他臨時職責 需要時能出差

資歷：

學士或以上學歷，主修工商管理。有內地留學經歷優先; 歡迎應屆畢業生。
必須中文書寫能力強，具備優良寫作技巧及了解內地商業文化;
可考慮沒有工作經驗
如具有文化旅遊工作經驗優先;
普通話母語優先及具廣東話溝通能力，良好的口語和書面英語;
能夠獨立工作，有責任心，注重細節，有團隊精神 有禮，開朗及主動，有動力;
需具備表達個人意見能力;
具良好的溝通和人際交往能力
有高度的誠信、專業、成長的意願，能夠在快節奏的環境中工作，並能夠滿足最後期限
精通電腦MS Office，包括Word，Excel，PowerPoint

Manage personal and corporate MPF/financial accounts;
Provide after-sale services and client protection services;
Build up a professional team for a lifetime career path.
Reward Package

Salary point will be $15,000 +  monthly bonus (included month allowance, performance bonus, annual bonus);
Luxury rewards for each half year / year goal (eg. famous brand jewellery, electronic product);
Flexible working days and hours;
Excellent career development and promotion opportunities;
Medical scheme & study allowance.
Requirement


HKDSE equivalent and above, degree holder is highly preferable;
IANG also will be considered;
No relevant experience is required - Self-motivated, positive attitude, and customer-oriented.

To Apply

Interested applications please send your detailed CV to nationsagencyhr @ gmail.com or contact  Carly Wan, HR Manager at 9823-1138.

Management Trainee (2022 intake) (Job ID 3235)
Position Summary
Through BEA's two-year Management Trainee ("MT") programme, you'll have a chance to become one of the future leaders at BEA. Working with the Bank's extensive overseas network, you'll gain in-depth knowledge of core banking functions as well as exposure to the China market and international banking. Once you've completed the programme, having demonstrated strong potential and met the management benchmarks, you'll be advanced to an executive position.
Requirements
Bachelor's degree (honours) or above from a reputable university (local or overseas), with no more than two years of work experience;
Self-motivated, mature, and possessing a strong drive for excellence;
Good team player and a natural leader;
Excellent communication and analytical skills;
Excellent command of English, Cantonese, and Putonghua; and
Passionately committed to developing a long-term career in the banking industry.
(Candidate is not required to upload CV at this moment.  Please input your information in the system.)
Please apply online via the BEA Careers website at https://careers.hkbea.com/psp/hcmprd/EMPLOYEE/HRMS/c/HRS_HRAM.HRS_APP_SCHJOB.GBL?Page=HRS_APP_JBPST&Action=UFOCUS=Applicant&SiteId=1&JobOpeningId=3235&PostingSeq=1 or by clicking the "Apply Now" button below. Kindly note that if you are a new user, you have to first create your User Profile before you can apply.
Personal data provided by job applicants will be used for recruitment purposes only and will be treated in accordance with the Bank's Personal Information Collection (Employees) Statement and Privacy Policy Statement. Applicants who are not invited for interviews within six weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and the personal data collected will be destroyed after six months.
